4 mages with new pets<br>
1 Epic mage Pet<br>
1 Shaman.<br>
<br>
Since the Epic pet is lower level it holds agro like a charm, keep taunt on and it will never loose agro, turn taunt off for new pets.  The fact that it has a sick DS and higher HP help a lot.   New pets hit sslightly harder but dont have the HP or the DS.    <br>
<br>
Shaman slows mob, and heals pets when / if needed. Throws in his own pets or nukes for fun.<br>
<br>
If anything lives more then 30 seconds its a shock. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nanamarinfernostorm>Nanamar Infernostorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 507<br> <font color=#333333>(10/31/02 11:35:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: All Mage Group or Almost</span><hr size=1> I did trial of exe in POJ w/ 3 mages 1 ranger 1 war 1 cleric <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Master Nanamar Infernostorm<br>
